16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-702.1 of Title 63, unless
19 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 No public trust hospital license or main provider location under
21 a provider agreement with the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid
22 Services (CMS), as provided for under 42 C.F.R., Sections 489.1
23 through 489.18, shall be transferred from its current address to an
24 address greater than fifteen (15) miles away, if the public trust
