1 hosp ital is located in a community with a population of fewer than
2 thirty thousand (30,000) residents, according to the latest Federal
3 Decennial Census. If a public trust hospital facility announces a
4 closure, before the closure of the facility, a mediator shall be
5 appointed. The municipality beneficiary of the public trust
6 hospital shall also appoint a mediator. The two mediators shall
7 appoint a mutually agreed-upon third mediator. The three mediators
8 shall agree upon a sales price for the hospital, in accordance with
9 appropriate due diligence and financial audits received from the
10 public trust hospital, if the hospital and the municipality cannot
11 agree without mediation. The hospital shall be transferred to the
12 beneficiary municipality if the beneficiary municipality is willing
13 to pay the agreed-upon purchase price set forth by the mediators and
14 has the appropriate staff identified to operate the hospital.
15 In the event the public trust hospital is sold to another
16 entity, the trustees of the hospital shall certify that they have
17 not entered into any agreement, formal or informal, with the
18 prospective owners of the hospital regarding any position, role, or
19 employment for themselves or their direct relatives, and they shall
20 also certify that they have not and will not receive any financial
21 benefit from the prospective owners, whether in-kind or otherwise.
22 In the event a public, third party, has been leasing the public
23 trust hospital and operating the public trust hospital under a
24 lease, upon termination of that lease, the hospital CMS provider
